Abstract = {{A key feature of parenting is that it is observable starting from
   behaviors that are performed daily by adult caregivers during repeated
   interactions with the child. Functional magnetic resonance imaging
   (fMRI) research on parental brain should integrate settings that
   resemble ecologies of situations in which parents typically care for
   children. However, as our commentators point out, ecological settings in
   fMRI research are challenging and require a multiperspective approach
   that systematically considers psychological and behavioral complexities
   of ``mommy brain{''} to better understand how contingent mental states
   of mothers articulate with specific multi-tasking situations.}},
